    bibo:volume "5213" ;
    dc:creator "Allsopp, Peter G." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Australian Melolonthini (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae): reclassification of eight species to Antitrogus Burmeister, 1855 and Barryfilius new genus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381672>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381690>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381682> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381672>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–6. Setal and scale types on pronota of Australian Melolonthini. 1, White, rounded scales, contained within the puncture—Lepidiota podicalis Moser, 1913; 2, white, elongate setae, largely contained within the puncture—Hypolepida wilsoni Britton, 1978; 3, white, elongate setae, longer than the puncture—Antitrogus ciliatus (Britton, 1978); 4, mixture of long setae and white, flattened setae—Allothnonius barretti Britton, 1978; 5, long thin, yellow-brown setae—Rhopaea decipennis Lea, 1919; 6, recumbent, flattened, tapered, finely pointed setae—Holorhopaea sagata Britton, 1978. Figs. 1, 5 by SAM; Figs. 2–4 by Queensland Museum; Fig. 6 reproduced from Weir et al. (2019) (CSIRO, used with permission)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7381672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381690>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26–28. Lectotype of Lepidiota oblonga Brenske, 1900. 26, Dorsal view; 27, ventral view; 28, labels. Photographs by Museum für Naturkunde." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7381690/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7381682>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–18. Adult males of Barryfilius species, dorsal views. 14, Barryfilius contiguus (Britton, 1978); 15, B. laevis (Arrow, 1932); 16, B. lewisae (Britton, 1978); 17, B. quinarius (Britton, 1978); 18, B. vernus (Britton, 1978). Photographs by Greg Daniels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7381682/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

